7 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to elections; prohibiting persons who
are not a qualified elector from filing as a
9 candidate for any municipal office; prohibiting
nonqualified electors from being appointed to any
10 unexpired term for elected municipal office; amending
26 O.S. 2021, Section 5-105, as amended by Section 1,
11 Chapter 43, O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
5-105), which relates to registration requirements
12 for candidates for state or county office; requiring
candidates to be qualified electors; prohibiting
13 nonqualified electors from being appointed to any
unexpired term for elected state or county office;
14 prohibiting nonqualified electors from being elected
to or serving on a board of education for a school
15 district or technology center school district;
prohibiting nonqualified electors from being
16 appointed to any unexpired term for elected school
district or technology center school district office;
17 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 16-115 of Title 11, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 16770 Page 1

1 No person who is not a qualified elector as described in Section
2 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution may file as a
3 candidate for any municipal office. Such persons shall also be
4 prohibited from appointment to any unexpired term of any elected
5 municipal office.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 5-105, as
7 amended by Section 1, Chapter 43, O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025,
8 Section 5-105), is amended to read as follows:
9 Section 5-105. A. To file as a candidate for nomination by a
10 political party to any state or county office, a person must have
11 been a registered voter of that party for the six-month period
12 immediately preceding the first day of the filing period prescribed
13 by law and, under oath, so state. Provided, this requirement shall
14 not apply to a candidate for the nomination of a political party
15 which attains recognition less than six (6) months preceding the
16 first day of the filing period required by law. However, the
17 candidate shall be required to have registered with the newly
18 recognized party within fifteen (15) days after such party
19 recognition.
20 B. To file as an independent candidate for any state or county
21 office, a person must have been registered to vote as an independent
22 for the six-month period immediately preceding the first day of the
23 filing period prescribed by law and, under oath, so state.
24
Req. No. 16770 Page 2

1 C. To file as a candidate under either subsection A or B of
2 this section, a candidate must be a qualified elector as described
3 in Section 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution.
4 D. No person who is not a qualified elector as described in
5 Section 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution may be
6 appointed to any unexpired term of any elected state or county
7 office.
8 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13A-112 of Title 26, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 No person may be elected to a board of education of a school
12 district or technology center school district who is not a qualified
13 elector as described in Section 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma
14 Constitution. Such persons shall be prohibited from appointment to
15 any unexpired term of any elected board of education of a school
16 district or technology center school district office.
17 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
